Prince Lethukuthula Zulu JOHANNESBURG - Five suspects allegedly involved in the murder of Prince Lethukuthula Zulu have been arrested. The 50-year-old Prince was murdered two weeks ago. READ: Prince Lethukuthula Zulu to be laid to rest Security guards discovered the prince's body at his residence in Northwold on the 6th of this month. The five suspects, four women, and one man were arrested in Pretoria, on Friday. One of the suspects was also found in possession of substances normally used by drug victims. Police also seized stolen items. The suspects are facing charges of murder and theft. READ: Family mourns Zulu Prince's death They are expected to appear in the Randburg Magistrate's court on Monday. Prince Lethukuthula Zulu was the firstborn son of King Goodwill Zwelithini kaBhekuzulu.